This paper deals with automated image analysis and linguistic annotation of pictures, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques, such as zero-shot learning and distributional semantics, which are commonly used in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the improvement in supervised object recognition, which suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
